# Cloudflare Pages routing — R1 (ADR 0040): marketing landing at /, editor SPA at /app.
#
# Real files (/, /privacy, /terms, /site.css, /og-image.png, /static/*, …) are
# served directly and take precedence over these rules, so only non-file paths
# fall through here. `/app` resolves to app.html via Pages' clean-URL handling;
# the explicit rules below cover client-side deep routes and legacy links.

# Preserve legacy share links minted before R1: /display/… → /app/display/…
/display/*   /app/display/:splat   301

# Editor SPA shell for /app and any client-side route beneath it (hard refresh).
/app         /app.html             200
/app/*       /app.html             200

# Anything else that is not a real file is a genuine 404 (not the landing).
/*           /404.html             404
